Property.preferredName: Strong Cytochrome P450 3A4 Induction Medication Eligibility Determination
Property.preferredDefinition: Having strength, power, or intensity greater than average or expected.:Induced primarily in liver by glucocorticoids, drugs, pesticides, and carcinogens and encoded by human CYP3A4 Gene (Cytochrome P450 IIIA Subfamily), Cytochrome P450 3A4 is a 502-amino acid 57.3-kD membrane-bound ER heme-thiolate monooxygenase. CYP3A4 is involved in an NADPH-dependent electron transport pathway and phase I oxidative metabolism of carcinogens, steroids, fatty acids, and xenobiotics, as well as bioactivation of aflatoxin B(1) to a genotoxic derivative. Activity seems a key predictor of drug responsiveness and toxicity. (from LocusLink, Swiss-Prot, OMIM, and NCI):The act of bringing about something.:biologically active substance, including those intended for use in diagnosis, treatment, or prevention of disease or other abnormalities, for the relief of suffering, or control or improvement of a physical or mental state; includes biological products.:Criteria to determine eligibility of patients for medical care programs and services.

Concepts.definition: Having strength, power, or intensity greater than average or expected.
Cytochrome P450 3A4 (503 aa, ~57 kDa) is encoded by the human CYP3A4 gene. This protein is involved in the oxidation of steroids, fatty acids and xenobiotics.
The act of bringing about something.

A drug product that contains one or more active and/or inactive ingredients; it is intended to treat, prevent or alleviate the symptoms of disease. This term does not refer to the individual ingredients that make up the product.
The act of determining if a subject is suitable for enrollment in a study according specific protocol criteria and procedures.

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 3
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is patient receiving CYP3A inhibitors such as ketoconazole and clarithromycin within 7 days prior to the first dose of navitoclax or during navitoclax administration?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Does patient require chronic
ReferenceDocuments.description: Does patient require chronic concomitant treatment of strong CYP3A4 inducers (e.g., dexamethasone, phenytoin, carbamazepine, rifampin, rifabutin, rifapentin, phenobarbital, and St. John's Wort)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 5
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is patient receiving any medications or substances that are inhibitors or inducers of CYP450 enzymes, including St. John's wort or hyperforin (potent CYP3A4 enzyme inducer) and grapefruit juice (potent cytochrome P450 CYP3A4 enzyme inhibitor)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 4

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 2
ReferenceDocuments.description: Does patient require concomitant treatment of strong CYP3A4 inducers (e.g., dexamethasone, phenytoin, carbamazepine, rifampin, rifabutin, rifapentin, phenobarbital, and St. John's Wort)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 1

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 7
ReferenceDocuments.description: Does patient require chronic concomitant treatment of strong CYP3A4 inducers (e.g., dexamethasone, phenytoin, carbamazepine, rifampin, rifabutin, rifapentin, phenobarbital, and St. John's Wort) or inhibitors (eg. ketoconazole, miconazole, itraconazole, voriconazole, posaconazole, clarithromycin, telithromycin, indinavir, saquinavir, ritonavir, nelfinavir, amprenavir, fosamprenavir nefazodone, lopinavir, troleandomycin, mibefradil and conivaptan)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 8
ReferenceDocuments.description: Does patient require chronic concomitant treatment of strong CYP450 3A4 inducers (e.g., dexamethasone, phenytoin, carbamazepine, rifampin, rifabutin, rifapentin, phenobarbital, and St. John's Wort) or inhibitors (eg. ketoconazole, miconazole, itraconazole, voriconazole, posaconazole, clarithromycin, telithromycin, indinavir, saquinavir, ritonavir, nelfinavir, amprenavir, fosamprenavir nefazodone, lopinavir, troleandomycin, mibefradil and conivaptan)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 6
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is patient receiving any medications or substances that are inhibitors or inducers of CYP3A4, including herbal preparation containing CYP3A4 inducers (e.g., St. John's Wort), grapefruit and grapefruit juice (CYP3A4 inhibitor) within 2 weeks before the start of study treatment?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 11
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is patient receiving any medications or substances that are strong inhibitors or inducers of CYP3A4 enzymes, including St. John's wort or hyperforin (potent CYP3A4 enzyme inducer) and grapefruit juice (potent cytochrome P450 CYP3A4 enzyme inhibitor)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 10
ReferenceDocuments.description: Is patient receiving any medications or substances that are strong or moderate  inhibitors or inducers of CYP3A4 enzymes, including St. John's wort or hyperforin (potent CYP3A4 enzyme inducer) and grapefruit juice (potent cytochrome P450 CYP3A4 enzyme inhibitor)?

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 14

ReferenceDocuments.name: Theradex - 17
